In the figure, $ \angle EAB$ and $ \angle ABC$ are right angles. $ AB = 4, BC = 6, AE = 8$, and $ \overline{AC}$ and $ \overline{BE}$ intersect at $ D$. What is the difference between the areas of $ \triangle ADE$ and $ \triangle BDC$?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(4mm);
defaultpen(linewidth(.8pt)+fontsize(10pt));

pair A=(0,0), B=(4,0), C=(4,6), Ep=(0,8);
pair D=extension(A,C,Ep,B);

draw(A--C--B--A--Ep--B);
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,N);
label("$E$",Ep,N);
label("$D$",D,2.5*N);
label("$4$",midpoint(A--B),S);
label("$6$",midpoint(B--C),E);
label("$8$",(0,3),W);
\end{asy}
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ 2\qquad
\textbf{(B)}\ 4\qquad
\textbf{(C)}\ 5\qquad
\textbf{(D)}\ 8\qquad
\textbf{(E)}\ 9$
